Sentencas: In the present study, multiscale microstructure evolutions of nickel and gadolinium doped ceria (Ni-GDC) composite anode operated under humidified condition (800 degrees C, 40%H2O:20%H-2:40%N-2) are investigated.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Focused ion beam - scanning electron microscopy (FIB-SEM) with spatial resolutions of 2 nm and 25 nm are used to observe the changes in both local and whole microstructures.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Significant multiscale reorganization of the microstructure is observed in both Ni and GDC phases.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Migration of GDC nano-particles in the range of several micrometers is confirmed.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: In addition, thin GDC layer with nanometer thickness is formed on the Ni surface, similar to the strong metal support interaction (SMSI).
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Heterogeneous microstructural evolutions of the GDC phase are seen at the electrode-electrolyte interface and at the vicinity of the current collector.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The GDC microstructural evolution is considered as a key factor of anode degradation.
Titulo: Multiscale microstructural evolutions of nickel-gadolinium doped ceria in solid oxide fuel cell anode
